HEADWORD: Mesothelium
<hw>Mes`o*the"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>me`sos</grk> middle + E. epi<ets>thelium</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Epithelial mesoderm; a layer of cuboidal
epithelium cells, formed from a portion of the mesoderm during the
differetiation of the germ layers. It constitutes the boundary of the
c⟦oe⟧lum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesothoracic</ent>⟦br⟧
